## Required Output Format

Use EXACTLY these three sections. Be concise. Use bullet points. Reference specific plan sections/tasks by name or number. Provide short code/pseudo-code examples only when suggesting a concrete fix.

### CRITICAL EXECUTION RISKS
Ambiguities or missing details that will cause an AI agent to fail, guess wrong, or write bad code. Each item must quote the vague part of the plan and state what's missing.

### RULE VIOLATIONS
Direct conflicts with Team Engineering Rules above. Reference the rule number and the specific plan element that violates it.

### ARCHITECTURAL BLIND SPOTS
Concurrency, state management, coupling, or data integrity issues that the plan doesn't address. Only flag issues that are specific to THIS plan — no generic advice.

If a section has no issues, write "None found." Do not pad sections with generic advice.

